<br>
* Class specific stuff. Current officer poll results = Each person can win ONE item per raid on class specific items only.. You are then out for rolls for the rest of the raid to ensure winning of more guildies.  IF everyone there for the class has already won the item or has better and does not wish to roll; You can then have that item even if you have already had your one win for the night <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
* If the raid was called for the express purposes of getting a person an item, that person has the right to that item if it drops no matter what. Also, if a set of items were agreed upon before the raid starts to drop to go to someone (Like multiple reavers and torches in CoM) then those people get them. <br>
<br>
* If we are on a raid and an epic piece drops in that zone.. We will use the epic board as to who is closest to finishing their epic and the person closest that is present at the raid will get that piece UNLESS it is a specific scheduled event for that person<br>
<br>
* NBG: Need before Greed. If an item drops and its better than what you have, you have the right to roll on it if its rollable by your class. If you dont need it, DONT roll. Let a guildie with something lesser upgrade. <br>
<br>
* If its a full fledged raid, and a item drops that no one can use, it goes to the guild bank. <br>
<br>
* If its a full fledged raid, all plat goes to the guild bank. <br>
<br>
* If its a full fledged raid, all gems by clerics, necros, and mages (for others in raid's use) are to be re-imbersed by like items or by plat from the guild bank when the guildie requests it. Please keep track of it yourself as the guild bank has more important things to do. <br>
<br>
* If you won a roll that night, it is highly encouraged to pass down your old armor to a needful guildie or to the guild bank. However, this is NOT manditory. <br>
